parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power steering, brakes, and other critical systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Popping sounds from speakers
crackling noises
loud buzzing noise
black screen
no backup camera
no beeping when in reverse
no sound when blinkers or hazard lights are on
no radio
no power to front charger
no ability to use front auxiliary cable
liquid detected in the lightning connector
and sudden loss of electronics.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning door locks and electronics can cause safety issues for drivers and passengers, including inability to exit the vehicle, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Door locks malfunctioning
radio screen going black or glitching
music silencing
backup camera stopping
CarPlay not connecting
and air or heat not coming from the floor panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries, including whiplash, and can lead to loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Touchy brakes
brake pedal becoming extremely sensitive
and sudden stopping of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto-stop system and ignition issues can cause safety issues, including inability to turn off the vehicle, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: AUTO-STOP not functioning properly
keyless ignition button not turning off the vehicle
and check engine warning light and reduced power message displayed on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's electrical system can cause a fire hazard, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine smoking and a fire starting after a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake squealing and noise can be a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses. In some cases, the squealing may be a sign of a more serious underlying issue with the brake system.
symptoms: Brakes squeal or make a loud noise when applying the brakes
especially at low speeds or when in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Loss of Stopping Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time.
symptoms: Brakes require extreme pressure to stop the vehicle
brakes fail to stop the vehicle
or the vehicle takes longer than usual to come to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS and Stability Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and stability control systems can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop or stabilize properly.
symptoms: ABS and stability control systems crash or malfunction without warning
check engine light comes on
and brake system becomes ineffective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual noise can be a distraction to the driver and may be a sign of a more serious underlying issue with the brake system.
symptoms: Loud audible popping noise comes through the stereo system when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The turbocharger fails
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle's performance is decreased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to recognize the vehicle is in park can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "shift to park" message
the vehicle does not recognize it is in park
the message appears randomly but more frequently over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to accidents or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the vehicle will not start
warning lights flash on the dashboard
the wipers move back and forth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: A loud popping noise is heard through the stereo speakers
the rear backup camera view is fuzzy or shorts out
the Android Play feature shuts off and on on the screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The removal of the jack without a replacement can leave the vehicle without a necessary safety feature, making it difficult or impossible to change a wheel in the event of a flat tire.
symptoms: The vehicle no longer has a jack
the owner is left without a means to change a wheel.
